## Architecture Overview

### Clean Architecture

The backend follows Clean Architecture (Ports & Adapters). Each layer depends only inward — never outward.

```
Presentation → Application → Domain ← Infrastructure
```

- **Domain**: Pure business entities, value objects, and abstract repository interfaces. Zero external dependencies.
- **Application**: Use cases that orchestrate domain logic. Depends only on domain abstractions.
- **Infrastructure**: Concrete implementations — SQLAlchemy repositories, OAuth2 providers, email clients.
- **Presentation**: FastAPI routers and Pydantic schemas. Calls application use cases.

### Project Structure

```
backend/
├── src/
│   ├── domain/
│   │   ├── entities/           # Core business entities (pure Python, no DB)
│   │   ├── value_objects/      # Immutable domain values
│   │   └── repositories/       # Abstract repository interfaces (ABC)
│   ├── application/
│   │   ├── use_cases/          # One file per use case (e.g., create_appointment.py)
│   │   └── dtos/               # Input/output data transfer objects
│   ├── infrastructure/
│   │   ├── database/
│   │   │   ├── models.py       # SQLAlchemy ORM models
│   │   │   └── session.py      # Async engine and session factory
│   │   ├── repositories/       # Concrete SQLAlchemy repository implementations
│   │   ├── email/              # Email service interface (IEmailService) and Resend implementation
│   │   └── auth/               # OAuth2 provider clients, JWT utilities
│   ├── presentation/
│   │   ├── routers/            # FastAPI APIRouter modules by resource
│   │   └── schemas/            # Pydantic request/response schemas
│   ├── config.py               # Settings via pydantic-settings
│   └── main.py                 # FastAPI app creation and lifespan
├── tests/
│   ├── unit/                   # Unit tests (no DB, mocked dependencies)
│   ├── integration/            # Integration tests (real DB via test container or SQLite)
│   └── conftest.py             # Shared fixtures (app client, DB session)
├── alembic/
│   ├── versions/               # Migration files
│   └── env.py                  # Alembic configuration
├── pyproject.toml              # All project metadata and tool config
├── Dockerfile
└── .env.example
```

