## SOLID and DRY Principles

### Single Responsibility
Each class has one reason to change. Use cases contain business logic, repositories handle persistence, routers handle HTTP concerns.

### Open/Closed
Extend behavior by adding new use cases or new repository implementations, never by modifying existing ones.

### Dependency Inversion
All dependencies flow toward abstractions. Concrete implementations are injected via FastAPI `Depends` or constructor arguments — never instantiated inline.

### DRY
Common query patterns are extracted into base repository helpers. Shared Pydantic schemas are defined once and reused across routers.

