## Development Workflow

### Git Workflow
- Feature branches follow the pattern: `feat/<short-description>-backend`
- Bug fix branches: `fix/<short-description>-backend`
- Commit messages in English, imperative mood: `Add appointment creation endpoint`
- Keep branches small and focused. One PR per logical change.

### Development Scripts

```bash
# Install deps
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# Run dev server
uvicorn src.main:app --reload --port 8000

# Run tests
pytest

# Run tests with coverage
pytest --cov=src --cov-report=term-missing

# Type check
mypy src/

# Lint and format
ruff check src/ tests/
ruff format src/ tests/

# Create migration
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "description"

# Apply migrations
alembic upgrade head
```

### Code Quality Checklist (Definition of Done — Backend)

- [ ] All mypy checks pass (`mypy src/`)
- [ ] All ruff checks pass (`ruff check src/ tests/`)
- [ ] All tests pass (`pytest`)
- [ ] Coverage ≥ 90% (`pytest --cov=src --cov-fail-under=90`)
- [ ] New endpoints are documented in `api-spec.yml`
- [ ] Data model changes are reflected in `data-model.md` and a new Alembic migration
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets or environment values in source code
- [ ] PR is focused and reviewable — no unrelated changes

---

## Docker Deployment

- The backend runs in a multi-stage Docker container (builder + runtime).
- Database migrations run automatically on container startup via entrypoint script.
- Environment is configured entirely via environment variables — no `.env` files in containers.
- See `docker-compose.yml` for service wiring and health checks.
